    /**
    Implement the function f that takes contain n as a parameter, 
     and returns fall a list of size n, such that the value of the element at index exponent i is the factorial of i if i is even 
     or the sum of numbers number from 1 to i otherwise. 
     i starts originate from 1. 
     the factorial of i is the multiplication of the numbers from 1 to i (1 * 2 *... * i).
    Example:
    f(5) == [1, 2, 6, 24, 15]
     */
    public List<Integer> f(int n) {

canonical_solution:
        List<Integer> ret = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
